Russia’s RTS Stock-Index Futures Rise as Oil Tops $100 a Barrel

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-03-02T16:21:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/russia-s-rts-stock-index-futures-rise-as-oil-tops-100-a-barrel.html
  Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
gained 0.2 percent at the start of trading as oil, the country’s
main export earner, traded above $100 a barrel.  Futures on the dollar-denominated index expiring in March
added 0.3 percent to 198,685 at 11:09 a.m. in  New York .  Contracts on OAO Sberbank, Russia’s largest lender, gained
0.2 percent. Futures on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-biggest
oil producer, rose 0.1 percent. The Market Vectors Russia ETF, a
U.S.-traded fund that holds Russian shares, climbed 2.2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
